<!-- Begin content -->
<div id="page_content_wrapper" class="hasbg ">
	<div class="post_caption">
		<div class="post_info_cat">
		    		        	<a href="https://droneandslr.com/travel-blog/category/hawaii/">Hawaii</a>
		    		</div>
		<h1>Driving Along Oahu&#8217;s Scenic Coast</h1>
		<hr class="title_break"/>
				<br class="clear"/>
		<div class="post_detail">
			<span class="post_info_date">
		    	3rd December 2018			</span>
		</div>
			</div>    
    <div class="inner">

    	<!-- Begin main content -->
    	<div class="inner_wrapper">

    		<div class="sidebar_content">
					
						
<!-- Begin each blog post -->
<div id="post-7136" class="post-7136 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-hawaii tag-hawaii tag-north-shore-ohau-things-to-do tag-oahu-beaches tag-road-trip">

	<div class="post_wrapper">
	    
	    <div class="post_content_wrapper">
	    
	    			    
		    				    <div class="post_header">
				    
				    <p>The best way to discover the beauty of Oahu is to drive along the island&#8217;s scenic coastline. The day we arrived at Oahu, after spending an incredible time on the <a href="https://droneandslr.com/travel-photography/big-island-hawaii/">Big Island</a>, we drove straight out of <a href="https://droneandslr.com/travel-photography/honolulu-hawaii/">Honolulu,</a> and away from its maddening crowds.</p>
<p><div class="video-container"><iframe class="lazy lazy-hidden" title="YouTube video player" width="" height=""  data-lazy-type="iframe" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dyqFi9Syj0k?theme=dark&rel=0&wmode=transparent" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe><noscript><iframe title="YouTube video player" width="" height="" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dyqFi9Syj0k?theme=dark&rel=0&wmode=transparent" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></noscript></div><br />
<em>Subscribe to my YouTube channel</em><br />
<script src="https://apis.google.com/js/platform.js"></script></p>
<div class="g-ytsubscribe" data-channelid="UCMq9XiFqyffXHidLhvpWElA" data-layout="full" data-count="hidden"></div>
<h2>Waikiki To The North Shore</h2>
<p>The North Shore is the most beautiful area of Oahu. It&#8217;s less crowded, less touristy, and definitely less commercial.</p>
<p>There are several shuttles that run between Honolulu and the North Shore, but taking them means skipping out on seeing the best parts of the island. Also, if you were to take the shortest route between Waikiki and North Shore, you&#8217;d probably miss out on an incredibly scenic route.</p>
<p>So, if you plan to get to the North Shore from Honolulu, I highly recommend taking the <strong>long scenic way around.</strong> It&#8217;d probably take you 4x the time but you&#8217;ll get to discover Oahu&#8217;s beauty &#8211; its gorgeous beaches, iconic mountains, and coastline.</p>
<a class="button small " style="background-color:#458b74 !important;color:#ffffff !important;border:1px solid #458b74 !important;" onclick="window.open('https://www.discovercarhire.com/locations/usa-hawaii?a_aid=droneandslr', '_blank')">Search for the best car rental options in Oahu</a>
<h2>Oahu&#8217;s Scenic Drive Map</h2>
<p>Locals advised us that instead of heading north-west, <strong>head south-east to get to the North Shore</strong>. I know that that sounds counter-intuitive, but it&#8217;s the most scenic route.</p>
<p>The map below shows you the route they advised us to take.</p>
<div id="attachment_10318" style="width: 780px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Honolulu+International+Airport/Hanauma+Bay/Sandy+Beach,+Honolulu,+HI,+United+States/Makapuu+Beach+Park/Waimanalo+Beach,+HI,+United+States/Lanikai+Beach,+Kailua,+HI,+United+States/Kaaawa,+HI,+United+States/Kahana+Bay+Beach+Park/Punalu'u+Beach+Park/Laie/@21.4589218,-157.9312238,11z/am=t/data=!3m1!4b1!4m62!4m61!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c006f943168f55f:0x7ed111b1cbf331df!2m2!1d-157.9250736!2d21.3245132!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c001273a5a0c3bf:0xe270349d165d1bfa!2m2!1d-157.6937919!2d21.2690358!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c001223e8ea8035:0xd2639b789c3e6f02!2m2!1d-157.6727427!2d21.285658!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c00117b634ebe1b:0x766c18df4268fba6!2m2!1d-157.6601154!2d21.311051!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c00139abcc803ad:0xa1d95d9f963aa8e4!2m2!1d-157.6870859!2d21.3307892!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c0014dd17442541:0x88415fbfd50f90b8!2m2!1d-157.7154355!2d21.3930921!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c0043fd1a9a9f87:0x68a7ffc214d47ad6!2m2!1d-157.8536111!2d21.5572221!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c0043f58b3ab115:0xbaf96689cd2d20ca!2m2!1d-157.8750491!2d21.5561753!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c0044418d736f65:0x366d3410a10b122b!2m2!1d-157.8860538!2d21.5802623!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c004542e04293fb:0xf8edf93e0b8b5b3!2m2!1d-157.9225549!2d21.6482858!3e0?shorturl=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-10318" class="lazy lazy-hidden wp-image-10318 size-full" src="//droneandslr.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/oahu-scenic-drive-route-1.jpg" alt="Oahu Scenic Drive 1/2" width="770" height="500" /><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-10318" class="wp-image-10318 size-full" src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/oahu-scenic-drive-route-1.jpg" alt="Oahu Scenic Drive 1/2" width="770" height="500" /></noscript></a><p id="caption-attachment-10318" class="wp-caption-text">Part 1 of the Oahu Scenic Drive</p></div>
<p>We split this scenic drive over a couple of days. <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/fn2AJ2hzqw72" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Our road trip started in Honolulu, and ended in Laie</a>, where we spent our first night. We drove from Waikiki to Hanauma Bay, all along the Windward Coast and finally to the North Shore. Along the way, we stopped at some stunningly pristine beaches, and drove between the mountains and the sea.</p>
<div id="attachment_10319" style="width: 725px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Laie/Turtle+Bay,+Hauula,+HI,+United+States/Banzai+Pipeline,+Haleiwa,+HI,+United+States/Sharks+Cove,+Pupukea,+HI,+United+States/Waimea+Bay+Beach+Park,+Kamehameha+Highway,+Haleiwa,+HI,+United+States/Laniakea+Beach,+Waialua,+HI,+United+States/Haleiwa,+HI,+United+States/Kaena+Point+Trail/Airport+Honolulu+Hotel,+North+Nimitz+Highway,+Honolulu,+HI,+United+States/@21.5201693,-158.2178213,11z/am=t/data=!4m56!4m55!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c004542e04293fb:0xf8edf93e0b8b5b3!2m2!1d-157.9225549!2d21.6482858!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c005055b3c6bc47:0xc2ee55ebd1ff9a8b!2m2!1d-157.9999643!2d21.7022589!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c0059fa0631d74b:0xaef8a2d808181351!2m2!1d-158.0512047!2d21.6650562!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c0059ec7041099f:0xab769ee3e345dc6f!2m2!1d-158.065!2d21.6547221!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c00599082b2115b:0x39f7c2ce689f8022!2m2!1d-158.0633629!2d21.639814!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c00591b3768cc4b:0x9cd5f1d61dbafc84!2m2!1d-158.0873414!2d21.6172053!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c0058cb4dbb9179:0xa24ef2e2df99f0c7!2m2!1d-158.1034112!2d21.5927614!1m5!1m1!1s0x0:0xd65893d0e3f1219b!2m2!1d-158.2372239!2d21.5794516!1m5!1m1!1s0x7c006fa7f11c8c81:0x42d32c2d4d022d9d!2m2!1d-157.9176265!2d21.336955!3e0?shorturl=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-10319" class="lazy lazy-hidden wp-image-10319 size-full" src="//droneandslr.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/oahu-scenic-drive-route-2.jpg" alt="Oahu Scenic Drive 2/2" width="715" height="490" /><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-10319" class="wp-image-10319 size-full" src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/oahu-scenic-drive-route-2.jpg" alt="Oahu Scenic Drive 2/2" width="715" height="490" /></noscript></a><p id="caption-attachment-10319" class="wp-caption-text">Part 2 of the Oahu Scenic Drive</p></div>
<p>For the next couple of days, Laie served as our base as we drove around the North Shore all the way to the western tip of Oahu, <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/iue2adFVBS92" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">before heading back to Honolulu</a>. By spending a couple of nights on the North Shore, we were able to really take our time discovering Oahu&#8217;s coastline.</p>
<h3>Hotels around North Shore</h3>
<p>I personally would advise you to <strong>spend a couple of nights at the North Shore</strong>, or in the vicinity of the North Shore. This gives you a chance to not only enjoy this scenic drive, but also appreciate the beauty of North Shore at a more gentle pace.</p>
<div class="googlefont" style="font-family:Alex Brush;font-size:30px;">Luxury</div>
<p>&lt;US$ 300</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://www.booking.com/hotel/us/turtle-bay-resort.en.html?aid=1339046&amp;no_rooms=1&amp;group_adults=2&amp;room1=A%2CA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><b>Turtle Bay Resort</b></a> &#8211; Iconic luxury property on the North Shore that&#8217;s been featured in numerous Hollywood movies. The resort is like a small town, and offers practically every facility. Great for families!</li>
<li><a href="https://www.booking.com/hotel/us/courtyard-by-marriott-oahu-north-shore.en.html?aid=1339046&amp;no_rooms=1&amp;group_adults=2&amp;room1=A%2CA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>Courtyard by Marriott Oahu North Shore</strong></a> &#8211; Relatively new hotel near North Shore. This is where we broke our scenic drive on the first night.</li>
</ol>
<div class="googlefont" style="font-family:Alex Brush;font-size:30px;">Mid-Range</div>
<p>&gt;US$ 200</p>
<p><a href="https://www.booking.com/hotel/us/hale-o-kaunala.en.html?aid=1339046&amp;no_rooms=1&amp;group_adults=2&amp;room1=A%2CA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>Hale O Kaunala</strong></a> &#8211; Fantastic location, a few minutes walk from the beautiful beaches of North Shore and the famous Ted&#8217;s Bakery. Great reviews!</p>
<div class="googlefont" style="font-family:Alex Brush;font-size:30px;">Budget Friendly</div>
<p>&gt;US$ 100</p>
<p><a href="https://www.booking.com/hotel/us/bentobox.en.html?aid=1339046&amp;no_rooms=1&amp;group_adults=2&amp;room1=A%2CA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>Aloha Wahiawa</strong></a> &#8211; Located in the town of Wahiawa, a 20-30 minute drive from the North Shore.</p>
<p>This part of the island is just so beautiful that it&#8217;d be a mistake to not spend a couple of days exploring it. Also, check out some of the deals on hotels in the North Shore.<br />
<ins class="bookingaff" data-aid="1627796" data-target_aid="1627796" data-prod="dfl2" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" data-lang="en" data-dest_id="6149" data-dest_type="region" data-df_num_properties="5"><br />
<!-- Anything inside will go away once widget is loaded. --><br />
<a href="//www.booking.com?aid=1627796">Booking.com</a><br />
</ins><br />
