<h2>Sandy Beach</h2>
<p>Sandy Beach is one of the most popular beaches for surfers in Honolulu. The waves here are among the strongest. We were warned by several people that we shouldn&#8217;t try and risk swimming at Sandy Beach. Apparently, a surfer had lost his life just the day before 🙁</p>
<div id="attachment_6805" style="width: 1210px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/sandy-beach-honolulu-oahu-hawaii-2.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-6805" class="lazy lazy-hidden wp-image-6805 size-full" src="//droneandslr.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/sandy-beach-honolulu-oahu-hawaii-2.jpg" alt="Sandy Beach as seen from the Halona Blowhole Lookout" width="1200" height="795" /><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-6805" class="wp-image-6805 size-full" src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/sandy-beach-honolulu-oahu-hawaii-2.jpg" alt="Sandy Beach as seen from the Halona Blowhole Lookout" width="1200" height="795" /></noscript></a><p id="caption-attachment-6805" class="wp-caption-text">Sandy Beach as seen from the Halona Blowhole Lookout</p></div>
<h2>Halona Blowhole Lookout</h2>
<p>Just before Sandy Beach is the Halona Blowhole Lookout. The powerful waves around this area really make for a beautiful blowhole. The view from the lookout too is spectacular.</p>
<div id="attachment_6808" style="width: 1210px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/halona-blowhole-oahu-hawaii.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-6808" class="lazy lazy-hidden wp-image-6808 size-full" src="//droneandslr.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/halona-blowhole-oahu-hawaii.jpg" alt="The Halona Blowhole" width="1200" height="675" /><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-6808" class="wp-image-6808 size-full" src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/halona-blowhole-oahu-hawaii.jpg" alt="The Halona Blowhole" width="1200" height="675" /></noscript></a><p id="caption-attachment-6808" class="wp-caption-text">The Halona Blowhole (please do not attempt what this couple is doing in the photo)</p></div>
<p>Do not ignore the signs and go down to the blowhole. It&#8217;s extremely dangerous and unpredictable.</p>
<h2>Waimanlo Beach</h2>
<p>This was probably one of my favourite beaches along the drive. The vast expanse of white sand, blue water, and mountains made this beach feel so big, yet so cozy. I could imagine myself sitting on this beach reading a book (which I did see someone else doing). And I would have done it had it not been for the fact we had a long way to go before our hotel.</p>
<p>Waimanlo Beach was the <strong>perfect</strong> beach in my opinion.</p>

