<h2>The Short Drive Back To Honolulu</h2>
<p>On our way back from the North Shore to Honolulu, we drove back along the main freeway. We were disappointed at how quickly we arrived in Honolulu. So yeah, we wouldn&#8217;t advise that you drive this way to the North Shore from Waikiki.</p>
<p>When we drove up to the North Shore, it had literally taken us 6 hours with all the stops. The time taken had given us a sense of space between Honolulu and the North Shore. On our way back, it took us under an hour to get back to the airport. This made us realise that we weren&#8217;t really that far away after all. North Shore just feels like a different world when compared to <a href="https://droneandslr.com/travel-photography/honolulu-hawaii/">Honolulu</a>, and downtown Waikiki.</p>
<div class="teaser_wrapper one center" style="background-color:#a8e6cf;"><img class="lazy lazy-hidden" src="//droneandslr.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/honolulu-oahu-hawaii-8.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="781" /><noscript><img src="https://droneandslr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/honolulu-oahu-hawaii-8.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="781" /></noscript><div class="teaser_content_wrapper"><h5 style="">Get The All-Inclusive Pass for Oahu's Top Attractions</h5><div class="teaser_content"><strong>Go Oahu® Card</strong><br />
